@tailrec

[source, scala]
----
def factorial(n: Int): Int = { // <1>
    def go(n: Int, acc: Int): Int = // <2>
        if (n <= 0) acc
        else go(n-1, n*acc)

    go(n, 1)
}
----
<1> Int is another primitive type in Scala, representing 32-bit integers
<2> An inner or local function

